<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B18FFD5FA1BF165F8AAFE80" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="518" pageId="6" pageNumber="517" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B18FFD4FA1BF165F98AF259" blockId="6.[1422,2626,3348,3469]" pageId="6" pageNumber="517">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B18FFD4FA1BF165F9BAF2E9" bold="true" box="[1423,1578,3348,3381]" pageId="6" pageNumber="517">Taxonomy.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B18FFD4F9A8F165F7CAF2E9" authority="de Blainville, 1826" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[1596,2138,3348,3381]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="6" pageNumber="517" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">Ctenomys brasiliensis de Blainville, 1826</taxonomicName>
, 
<materialsCitation id="61F1F00F1B18FFD4F7FAF165F98AF259" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798388324" pageId="6" pageNumber="517">“des parties intérieures du Brésil de la province de Las Minas.” Corrected by C. J. Bidau in 2015 to “Minas, Lavalleja, Uruguay.”</materialsCitation>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B19FFD5FCBAFD62FAEAFD62" blockId="7.[813,1407,275,702]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">
H. M. D. de Blainville thought the type locality was Minas Gerais State in southeastern Brazil, which is outside of the currently known distribution of any species of 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FCCFFDC5FC42FE0D" authorityName="Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[859,978,436,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">Ctenomys</taxonomicName>
, but 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FBBEFDC5FB70FE0D" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[1066,1248,436,465]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">C. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
was never collected again in that State. Using geometric morphometrics to compare skull of the 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FC1EFE57FBAAFD9B" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[906,1082,550,583]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">C. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
holotype with those of similar species, and taking into account the tag information, it was possible to rediscover the type locality of 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FB57FED0FAE6FD62" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[1219,1398,673,702]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">C. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D126FA521B19FFD5FF5CFEB6F8AAFE80" blockId="7.[200,1404,711,858]" lastBlockId="7.[1474,2680,281,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">
There is no doubt that the specimen was collected in Minas in Lavalleja Department, Uruguay. Now, there are only populations of 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FC21FE9AFBD6FCD0" authorityName="Lessa &amp; Langguth" authorityYear="1983" box="[949,1094,747,780]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="pearsoni">C. pearsoni</taxonomicName>
in the area along the southern coast of Uruguay. Further studies should be made to better understand taxonomic relationship between the C. pearson: complex and 
<taxonomicName id="169981D11B19FFD5FBACFF4CFB7DFC86" authorityName="de Blainville" authorityYear="1826" box="[1080,1261,829,858]" class="Mammalia" family="Ctenomyidae" genus="Ctenomys" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rodentia" pageId="7" pageNumber="25" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="brasiliensis">C. brasiliensis</taxonomicName>
—the type specimen for the genus that was collected in Uruguay and never occurred in southeastern Brazil. Monotypic.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B19FFD5FA50FD19F9E6FE76" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" type="distribution">
<caption id="85E6AADA1B19FFD5FA50FD19F9E6FE76" ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6588228" ID-Zenodo-Dep="6588228" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6588228/files/figure.png" inLine="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" targetBox="[197,789,282,697]" targetPageId="7">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B19FFD5FA50FD19F9E6FE76" blockId="7.[1474,2680,281,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B19FFD5FA50FD19F9E4FE59" bold="true" box="[1476,1652,360,389]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">Distribution.</emphasis>
S Uruguay, known only from the type locality in Las Minas, Lavalleja Department.
</paragraph>
</caption>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="9983A9D91B19FFD5FA50FDC3F95EFDFD" pageId="7" pageNumber="518" type="description">
<paragraph id="D126FA521B19FFD5FA50FDC3F95EFDFD" blockId="7.[1474,2680,281,861]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">
<emphasis id="E3ED26401B19FFD5FA50FDC3F92DFE0F" bold="true" box="[1476,1725,434,467]" pageId="7" pageNumber="518">Descriptive notes.</emphasis>
